				<h2 class="title"><a name="cookiedoughfudge">Cookie Dough Fudge</a><span class="d-easy">&nbsp;easy&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;medium&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;hard</span></h2>
				<div class="entry">
<img src="images/recipes/cookiedoughfudge.jpg" alt="Cookie dough fudge recipe" />

<p><pre>
3 cups sugar
1 1/4 cups milk
1/4 cup light corn syrup
2 tbsp butter
2 tsp vanilla
3/4 cup of diced cookie dough (1/4 inch cubes)
</pre></p>
<p>
Line an 8 inch square pan with foil and spray the foil with cooking spray. Alternatively, butter the pan.
</p><p>
In a large 3 quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook to 238F on candy thermometer (soft ball stage). Do not stir.
Remove from heat. Do not stir.
</p><p>
Cool to 120F. Add vanilla and cookie dough. Beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss. Quickly pour into greased pan.
</p>
